REV. 11/84
3 OZARK AIR LINES
DC-9 AND MD-82 FAN JET
Emergency Evacuation/Passenger Information
l/s MD -82 ONLY
NO SMOKING
IN THE LAVATORIES
CARRYON BAGGAGE. Federal regulations require all carryon baggage to
be stowed during takeoff and landing. These items must be placed under
the seat in front of you unless you are riding in an aircraft with enclosed
overhead compartments.
All other overhead racks may be used only for
such items as coats and hats.
Should you require assistance, please ask
your flight attendant about the stowage of these items.
OZARK AIR LINES would like to remind its passengers that federal regula-
tions prohibit the use of portable electronic devices on board aircraft.
Radios and other electronic equipment may not be operated during the
flight as they might interfere with navigation and communications equip-
ment. This does not, however, apply to the following devices: Portable
voice recorders,
tape players, hearing aids,
heart pacemakers,
electric
shavers, electronic watches or hand-held, solid state, electronic calculators
or games.
SEAT CUSHIONS. The seat cushion of each passenger seat is an ap-
proved flotation device and may be used in the event a ditching operation
should become necessary.
CIGARETTE LIGHTERS. We would like to caution our customers who
may have cigarette lighters with the visual fluid reservoir. Under the chang-
ing conditions of the cabin it is sometimes possible to have a very large
flame due to a pressure buildup in this reservoir. We would advise against
the use of this type lighter on board the aircraft.
SMOKERS. To ensure the comfort of all passengers, smoking is prohibited
in certain parts of the cabin at all times. Pipe and cigar smoking are also pro-
hibited. If you desire to smoke and are in a seat where it is not allowed,
check with the flight attendant to change. Of course, smoking is prohibited
in all areas during takeoff and landing.
